  <thing id="raUSikarRa" name="Sikari Rage" description="When a creature is damaged by a Sikari macaque swarm, it must succeed at a DC 17 Fortitude save or be affected as if by the spells confusion and rage-a kind of blind fury known as Sikari rage. These effects last for 1d6 rounds, and the effects of multiple bites are cumulative.\n\nWhile the fast-acting nature of this effect is similar to a poison, it is actually a disease, and the spell remove disease immediately ends the effects. Creatures that are immune to disease are also immune to this ability. The save DC is Constitution-based." compset="RaceSpec">
